WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:04.792
You are listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

00:05.293 --> 00:11.784
For more information about First Baptist, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWS.org.

00:14.348 --> 00:17.554
Today's message comes from Senior Pastor, Dr. Bob McCartney.

00:18.082 --> 00:19.945
Good morning and welcome to all of you.

00:20.005 --> 00:25.193
Welcome to those of you joining us at the church at Shepherd at our west campus and at 11 o'clock east.

00:25.213 --> 00:27.557
We're so glad that you're with us this morning.

00:28.218 --> 00:32.185
And I'm really happy that you're here to share in this Christmas celebration.

00:32.545 --> 00:35.570
We're in the midst of a series of messages called remember.

00:35.714 --> 00:41.122
And what we wanna do is remember the real meaning and message and mission of Christmas.

00:41.643 --> 00:54.483
So this morning we're gonna open our Bibles to Luke chapter 19 verse 10, one verse of scripture, but I do have several others that I'm gonna refer to as we move through this particular message this morning.

00:55.103 --> 00:56.045
I'm really disappointed.

00:56.566 --> 01:00.632
I'm just so disappointed because I announced the scripture passage and I got nothing.

01:01.313 --> 01:03.236
I got nothing, okay?

01:03.256 --> 01:04.658
So we're gonna do that again.

01:05.218 --> 01:07.461
I'm going to read Luke 1910.

01:09.664 --> 01:10.585
That's much better.

01:10.645 --> 01:12.127
I'm really excited about that now.

01:12.167 --> 01:15.031
I was like, how am I going to get through this message if they don't do that?

01:15.071 --> 01:16.032
How do I get there?

01:16.052 --> 01:16.393
I don't know.

01:17.094 --> 01:19.797
Well, you know, there's a lot of prep that goes into Christmas.

01:19.838 --> 01:27.147
I mean, you think about the choir in the orchestra and the voices of Mobile, the amount of preparation that it takes for them to do something like this.

01:27.488 --> 01:29.170
You think about our own Christmases.

01:29.602 --> 01:32.246
There's just so much preparation that goes into it.

01:32.546 --> 01:39.175
You've got to go to the store and buy the food, and you've got to prepare the food for the meal, and you've got to go to the store, and you've got to go shopping, you've got to find the perfect gift.

01:39.415 --> 01:41.218
You've got to wrap the gifts.

01:41.578 --> 01:45.043
And in our household, there's all the decorating that goes on.

01:45.183 --> 01:46.946
I am the pack mule, basically.

01:47.306 --> 01:48.348
I don't do any decorating.

01:48.408 --> 01:53.775
I just haul the stuff out of the attic, bring the stuff into the house, take the empty crates back up.

01:53.795 --> 01:58.962
Everything else is done by my wife who does all the preparation for Christmas.

01:59.298 --> 02:00.860
The first Christmas was that way too.

02:01.661 --> 02:04.145
There was a lot of preparation that went into the first Christmas.

02:04.986 --> 02:07.790
I mean, there were hundreds and hundreds of years of prophecy.

02:08.591 --> 02:21.810
There were countless times in which God saved the lineage of the Messiah in which Jesus would be born and all of those generations that came, that proved the chain that

02:21.954 --> 02:25.578
went from David all the way to Jesus because he would be the son of David.

02:25.799 --> 02:38.534
There's all this preparation that goes into Christmas in order for Jesus to come, not for us to have a midwinter festival, not for us to enjoy some nice music, not for us to even be with our family and friends.

02:39.776 --> 02:41.698
Jesus came on a rescue mission.

02:42.459 --> 02:46.163
You see, the mission of Christmas is a rescue mission.

02:47.024 --> 02:51.570
Jesus says in Luke 19, 10, the son of man has come.

02:52.034 --> 02:56.439
to seek and to save that which is lost.

02:57.360 --> 03:04.368
Jesus came on a search and rescue mission for all of us, for lost humanity.

03:05.309 --> 03:13.958
And so this morning, I wanna explore that expression for just a few minutes, because I do think it's important for us to understand what Christmas is really all about.

03:14.819 --> 03:21.106
What Christmas is really all about is that God loves us so much, that God cares for you so much,

03:21.442 --> 03:31.912
And God demonstrates to you that you matter so much that He said His only begotten His one of a kind, unique son on a mission to rescue you.

03:32.973 --> 03:36.457
And I believe that that has to start with an understanding of a word in the Bible.

03:36.917 --> 03:38.999
And it's a word that we would almost like to avoid.

03:39.600 --> 03:40.641
It is the word lost.

03:41.441 --> 03:46.046
You see, we need rescue because we are fallen and lost.

03:46.827 --> 03:48.368
That is why we need rescue.

03:48.909 --> 03:50.450
Jesus says He came

03:51.106 --> 03:54.130
to search and to save those who are lost.

03:54.711 --> 03:59.238
Now, when we use the word lost, we usually think it means like to misplace something.

03:59.258 --> 04:11.295
And there is a sense in which that's true in this word, but the Greek word that the New Testament is written in, the word that Jesus said for lost actually doesn't mean so much misplaced as it means ruined.

04:11.876 --> 04:13.038
It means destroyed.

04:13.318 --> 04:15.321
It means beyond repair.

04:15.882 --> 04:18.866
You see, sin didn't just wound us

04:19.138 --> 04:20.960
Sin wrecked us.

04:21.781 --> 04:22.883
That's what sin did.

04:23.644 --> 04:25.126
God creates his perfect world.

04:25.646 --> 04:30.653
He puts two sinless people in the world, Adam and Eve, and he gives them one commandment.

04:30.853 --> 04:34.638
You got one rule, and they promptly break it.

04:35.679 --> 04:45.792
And as a result of their rebellion against God, all of their offspring, which includes all of us, would inherit a sin nature.

04:45.852 --> 04:47.154
We would all

04:47.554 --> 04:50.459
become part of a fallen race.

04:51.060 --> 05:04.361
It is not as God intended, but God loves us so much that even there in the Garden of Eden, God said, I'm going to send a Savior.

05:05.843 --> 05:12.594
As God begins to tell Adam and Eve about the consequences of their sin, he also speaks to the serpent who attempted them.

05:13.154 --> 05:20.084
And in that moment, God says something to Adam and Eve and to the serpent that is really important.

05:20.665 --> 05:33.986
In Genesis chapter three, verse 15, he says, He will crush your head and you will only strike at his heel.

05:34.927 --> 05:39.854
He's saying, I'm going to send someone who will crush the power of the evil one.

05:39.874 --> 05:42.258
I'm going to send that one into this world.

05:43.138 --> 05:48.527
And you see, God sent his son to save us from our own lostness.

05:49.328 --> 05:51.932
We deny our lostness at our own peril.

05:51.972 --> 05:52.853
We are lost.

05:52.873 --> 05:54.236
We are not just exploring.

05:55.117 --> 05:56.259
We are sinful.

05:56.299 --> 05:58.322
We are not being our authentic selves.

05:58.923 --> 06:00.145
We are broken.

06:00.205 --> 06:01.868
We're not just on some journey.

06:02.649 --> 06:03.951
We are lost.

06:04.211 --> 06:05.634
We are wrecked.

06:05.654 --> 06:08.338
We are wounded beyond self-repair.

06:09.730 --> 06:14.337
This past Thanksgiving, there was a tragic story that came from West Texas.

06:15.358 --> 06:26.634
An elderly couple had left their home in Lubbock and gone to the small town of Panhandle, which is right outside Amarillo, and they went for a family gathering, but they left their cell phones at home.

06:27.435 --> 06:31.821
They forgot them, but hey, they had lived in a world without cell phone, so this shouldn't be any problem.

06:32.242 --> 06:35.186
They got to the family gathering, they enjoyed a great meal,

06:35.842 --> 06:39.167
enjoyed family time, the time came for them to go back to Lubbock.

06:39.207 --> 06:42.772
And so they left, hugged all their family and started on their journey.

06:43.854 --> 06:50.163
Well, after a while, the family began to worry because they hadn't called to say they made it home.

06:50.884 --> 06:55.771
So they started calling and after a little while, the family said, you know what, maybe they're on the side of the road, we're going to retrace.

06:55.991 --> 07:01.078
So they drove all the way to Lubbock, no sign of them anywhere on the road and they're not at home.

07:01.880 --> 07:03.602
They called the police and told them,

07:03.714 --> 07:06.397
that they were worried about their family member.

07:06.717 --> 07:14.246
It took a few hours because, you know, you can't just immediately put out a search, but after 24 hours, they started an official search.

07:14.266 --> 07:17.870
I mean, law enforcement agencies, everybody's looking for them.

07:17.890 --> 07:23.276
The long story short, five days later, there was a tragic ending.

07:24.057 --> 07:26.980
They found their car and they found their deceased bodies.

07:28.162 --> 07:31.986
In a remote pasture outside Tukumcari, New Mexico,

07:33.218 --> 07:42.048
Somewhere along the way, they took a wrong turn and got confused and wound up lost.

07:43.449 --> 07:50.517
You see, we like to think of lostness sometimes when we hear these messages and churches, someone who's defiant against God.

07:51.538 --> 07:54.321
You don't have to be defiant against God to be lost.

07:55.142 --> 07:56.203
You just have to drift.

07:57.765 --> 07:59.707
You just have to go your own way.

08:00.728 --> 08:02.130
And if you go your own way,

08:02.594 --> 08:06.498
You end up lost without any way to save yourself.

08:07.479 --> 08:09.141
This is the story of all of us.

08:09.842 --> 08:10.763
But here's the good news.

08:11.503 --> 08:14.607
Since we can't save ourselves, Christ had to come.

08:15.628 --> 08:22.715
See, not only are we lost, but the reason for our lostness is the Bible tells us repeatedly, we are dead in trespasses and sins.

08:24.257 --> 08:25.798
We're not just wounded, we're dead.

08:25.858 --> 08:29.362
In Colossians chapter 2 verse 13,

08:29.634 --> 08:38.246
When you were dead in your sins and the uncircumcision of your sinful nature, God made you alive with Christ.

08:39.388 --> 08:42.892
Dead people can't rescue themselves.

08:43.573 --> 08:45.035
They don't revive themselves.

08:45.075 --> 08:46.297
They can't call for help.

08:46.557 --> 08:48.620
They can't restore a broken relationship.

08:49.041 --> 08:50.743
And dead people don't seek God.

08:51.865 --> 08:58.514
The only thing you contribute to your salvation is the sin that made it necessary.

09:01.122 --> 09:07.554
We are dead in trespasses and sins and only Christ can make us alive again.

09:09.377 --> 09:16.230
You know, every now and then you'll see one of those stories on the news that's like from somewhere else and you're wondering why they put it on our news.

09:16.831 --> 09:21.119
Well, I saw one of those stories a couple of years ago and it really got my attention.

09:22.000 --> 09:25.106
And it was a story about a guy who was out

09:25.186 --> 09:26.929
In 2021, his name was Michael.

09:27.169 --> 09:31.315
He's in Rochester, Minnesota, and they had a massive snowstorm, and he's shoveling snow.

09:32.237 --> 09:37.104
And the story was about how easy it is to overexert yourself doing something like shoveling snow.

09:37.124 --> 09:42.171
You don't get really hot because it's snow and it's cold, but your heart really starts working.

09:42.652 --> 09:46.818
And all of a sudden, Michael's shoveling the snow, and he falls over face down in the snow.

09:47.800 --> 09:52.206
Thankfully, a neighbor saw him fall down and was watching it, and he realized he's not moving.

09:52.226 --> 09:54.610
He's not getting up, so the neighbor rushes across the street.

09:55.106 --> 09:56.567
He realizes he doesn't have a pulse.

09:56.587 --> 09:57.268
He's not breathing.

09:57.308 --> 09:58.309
He rolls Michael over.

09:58.629 --> 10:05.256
He starts CPR, grabs his cell phone, calls 911, the paramedics come while he's doing chest compressions on Michael.

10:05.316 --> 10:06.657
The paramedics take over.

10:06.697 --> 10:09.760
They take him to the hospital and Michael miraculously survives.

10:09.840 --> 10:12.142
But for 15 minutes, he didn't have a pulse.

10:13.944 --> 10:18.088
Some reporter ask him, and they're telling the story, trying to have people be cautious.

10:18.809 --> 10:24.594
And they ask him some inane question, and Michael responded like this.

10:25.378 --> 10:26.560
I did nothing.

10:27.622 --> 10:28.603
I was gone.

10:28.623 --> 10:30.927
They're the ones who brought me back.

10:32.069 --> 10:33.411
Let me explain something to you.

10:33.431 --> 10:37.237
You can do nothing to make yourself alive in Christ.

10:37.798 --> 10:38.198
Nothing.

10:39.260 --> 10:40.963
Only He can make you alive.

10:41.123 --> 10:44.388
Only Jesus can bring you back.

10:46.692 --> 10:53.042
Salvation through Christ is absolutely necessary because we are dead and our trespasses and sins.

10:53.442 --> 10:59.730
We're also told in this passage that Jesus alone can restore our broken relationship with God.

11:01.031 --> 11:03.014
Only Jesus can do this.

11:03.995 --> 11:22.898
You see, Christmas is not just the celebration of this wonderful truth and all the blessings that come because of Christmas, but Christmas also signals to us something that's very important, that salvation, eternal life, spending forever in a great place called heaven.

11:24.034 --> 11:30.280
is possible only through Jesus Christ, through Him and through Him alone.

11:31.662 --> 11:32.903
Jesus said these words.

11:33.664 --> 11:38.428
In John 14, 6, I am the way, the truth, the life.

11:39.289 --> 11:41.972
No one comes to the Father but through me.

11:44.374 --> 11:50.380
Other religions always say, here's what you must do to get to God.

11:51.361 --> 11:52.402
Here's what you must

11:52.546 --> 11:53.247
Perform.

11:53.287 --> 11:55.931
Here are the religious rituals that you have to go through.

11:55.991 --> 12:00.557
Here are the moral actions that you have to take to somehow get your way to God.

12:01.659 --> 12:07.367
And yet, if we're dead in our sins, we can't work our way anywhere.

12:08.809 --> 12:10.531
We can't get there on our own.

12:11.532 --> 12:14.156
We need a Savior and there is one and there's only one.

12:14.176 --> 12:16.459
You see, every other religion says, here's what you've got to do.

12:16.479 --> 12:16.880
You've got to do.

12:16.900 --> 12:17.741
You've got to do.

12:17.761 --> 12:20.224
Jesus says, here's what I came to do for you.

12:20.304 --> 12:21.426
Here's what I've done.

12:22.786 --> 12:25.409
He is the one and only Savior."

12:26.390 --> 12:34.337
The Bible echoes that in 1 Timothy 2, 5, Paul writes, for there is one God and one mediator between God and mankind, the man Christ Jesus.

12:35.078 --> 12:47.330
Peter said in a sermon in Acts 4, verse 12, for there is salvation in no one else, for there is no other name under heaven given to people by which we must be saved.

12:49.132 --> 12:51.314
Jesus is not a way to heaven.

12:52.194 --> 12:57.220
Jesus is the one and only way to heaven.

12:57.240 --> 12:57.780
He's it.

12:59.622 --> 13:00.984
The miracle is not.

13:02.446 --> 13:04.007
Oh, you mean there's only one way?

13:04.087 --> 13:05.409
No, the miracle is there's a way.

13:05.489 --> 13:08.092
There's a way.

13:08.132 --> 13:12.337
It just seems so narrow and judgmental.

13:13.338 --> 13:14.379
Don't you imagine something.

13:15.561 --> 13:16.882
You're in a building.

13:17.666 --> 13:22.152
Maybe an unfamiliar place, but all of a sudden you see smoke, and smoke begins to fill the hallways.

13:22.792 --> 13:27.017
And you're really unfamiliar with this building, so you're not exactly sure which way you should go to get out of the building.

13:27.538 --> 13:34.827
And you're confused, you become anxious, and maybe you're family with you, and you've got to get out of this building, and you're trying to figure out how to do it, and those hallways are filling up with smoke.

13:34.847 --> 13:46.962
When all of a sudden you hear this crash through a door, and there's a firefighter who comes the door, acts in hand, he's chopped through the door, and he looks at you and says, this is the only way out.

13:50.722 --> 13:51.643
That's not judgmental.

13:53.146 --> 13:54.167
That's clarity.

13:56.571 --> 13:58.734
You see, exclusivity is clarity.

14:00.096 --> 14:01.839
Exclusivity is also mercy.

14:03.682 --> 14:08.709
It is merciful to say there is one and only way and his name is Jesus.

14:10.973 --> 14:14.578
He is the way to life.

14:17.378 --> 14:21.246
You've been listening to a message from First Baptist Church, which is not false.

14:21.266 --> 14:29.923
For more information about First Baptist, including gathering times and locations, click the link in the show notes, or go to FBCWF.org.

14:30.284 --> 14:31.506
We'll see you next week.

